headline: Leadership Shakeup and Record AI Deals Could Be a Game Changer for Oracle (ORCL)
summary: In late September 2025, Oracle completed a major leadership transition, appointed Clay Magouyrk and Mike Sicilia as co-CEOs, and significantly expanded its cloud and AI infrastructure commitments with record-breaking contract wins and new data center initiatives for clients such as OpenAI. These rapid developments have positioned Oracle at the forefront of enterprise AI infrastructure, fueling heightened investor interest in the company's multi-year growth prospects as enterprises accelerate...

headline: Why Fears of a Trillion-Dollar AI Bubble Are Growing
summary: Tech firms are spending hundreds of billions of dollars on advanced chips and data centers, not just to keep pace with a surge in the use of chatbots such as ChatGPT, Gemini and Claude, but to make sure they’re ready to handle a more fundamental and disruptive shift of economic activity from humans to machines.  Since then, other tech rivals have ramped up spending, including Meta’s Mark Zuckerberg, who has pledged to invest hundreds of billions in data centers.
